opening up their wallets to prove it. The startup graveyard is littered wit=
h companies whose main value prop was privacy.=C2=A0
Instead, Truework [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkcuKxCAQRb8mLoOPaJK=
Fi4Ghf0OMVtIyUYOPCfn7Md0NA4UFdSnu9ZTRBbaYLnnEXND9qHIdIAOceYdSIKGaISlnJRF0Yn=
yYkZWDJROfkMtqTQBeu12WVAEdddmd0cXF8NrAmHL0lPOkJ85GakdO10EQYe2yGmIGOwu6Wvz21=
dU6CAYk_EK6YgC0y2cpR-7YV0cfrc7z7G-fM6af3kR_T9mjFq9yrMlAx75DLGqJyYWto-JWPFhX=
fVNOWLIr8Bkb7Q_tttAEnYozOyjM76KYEuTk3TDHglAuCO9JT9tErJaTkWkxrrT9gK-ALSMW5pn=
RbsB-o32uSy7avOKhJFucT5oB_zy1h_0lNE6qdV-DK5eCoJcd7BtheV_iBVVtECC1C1mly80fM8=
zHic-zeCNrjJnA00TFjJqzjW0r_Jv-AdeYoJM] needed to compete by building a bett=
er product with internet-native distribution that also happened to have pri=
vacy baked in. It needed to play the long game. It needed to be a Worldbuil=
der.=C2=A0
In Two Ways to Predict the Future [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkMG=
OhCAMQL9muGkABeHAYS_7GwalOGQUDNQ1_v0yY7KbUJq0aV77ZouwpHyZPRUk72_EawcT4SwrIE=
ImR4E8BmeY5KoTvSbO9I4poUgoo88Amw2rwXwA2Y9pDbPFkOJnglIuyNNoZfUkOZNSKOsn4MqzY=
dC99p2V3Kubaw8XIM5g4AfylSKQ1TwR9_Lovh78u77zPNuYcEo5xKWdUy3tNfBMzWmv0mBq9gwu=
zNjgExp_4JGBBMMpZ1RQybiQTLSs5bUivRNsqAsMnrvJCw_UdcyB1h1_9HRbeFuOqaCdXxW1kWz=
-0LX9etoN1k-jHj3WvB0x4DVCtNMK7vaBt9aPoXGBCLnqdqPFt0zaUTEoobW876_COkmV4lKTSn=
apTsV_6C-5Vo8u], I wrote that there are two ways that companies go after bi=
g markets. =E2=80=9CShotcallers find an obviously big market, guarantee tha=
t they=E2=80=99re going to transform it, and try to spend their way into ma=
king that happen.=E2=80=9D Worldbuilders, on the other hand:=C2=A0
Predict something non-obvious about the way the world is moving before othe=
rs see it and before the market is ready for their ultimate vision.
Create a wedge into the market and leverage it into a much larger opportuni=
ty. The public often ridicules or dismisses the initial wedge product.=C2=
=A0
They timestamp their vision, whether in public announcements or confidentia=
l documents.=C2=A0
Obvious Worldbuilders include Musk and Bezos. This video is classic Worldbu=
ilder:
Predict something non-obvious: Commerce on the internet is going to be mass=
ive.=C2=A0
Create a wedge: Books were not the biggest category, but they benefited the=
 most from the internet=E2=80=99s capabilities, and were the right category=
 in which to build the muscle.
Timestamp the vision: Bezos never said books are the end-all-be-all. He sai=
d that they were the =E2=80=9Cfirst and best product=E2=80=9D to sell onlin=
e.=C2=A0
Truework is a Worldbuilder, too.=C2=A0
Predict something non-obvious: As HR systems and lending move online, there=
=E2=80=99s an opportunity to build a privacy-first identity layer across th=
e internet.=C2=A0
Create a wedge: Employment and income verification is a vertical of identit=
y that everyone needs that has the least digital competition; it allows Tru=
ework to build up its most important asset: data.=C2=A0
Timestamp the vision: The team shared with me a 10-year vision that they se=
t out to accomplish in 2017. They=E2=80=99re executing on it almost perfect=
ly so far, and have big ambitions for the next six years.
Truework [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkcuKxCAQRb8mLoOPaJKFi4Ghf0OM=
VtIyUYOPCfn7Md0NA4UFdSnu9ZTRBbaYLnnEXND9qHIdIAOceYdSIKGaISlnJRF0YnyYkZWDJRO=
fkMtqTQBeu12WVAEdddmd0cXF8NrAmHL0lPOkJ85GakdO10EQYe2yGmIGOwu6Wvz21dU6CAYk_E=
K6YgC0y2cpR-7YV0cfrc7z7G-fM6af3kR_T9mjFq9yrMlAx75DLGqJyYWto-JWPFhXfVNOWLIr8=
Bkb7Q_tttAEnYozOyjM76KYEuTk3TDHglAuCO9JT9tErJaTkWkxrrT9gK-ALSMW5pnRbsB-o32u=
Sy7avOKhJFucT5oB_zy1h_0lNE6qdV-DK5eCoJcd7BtheV_iBVVtECC1C1mly80fM8zHic-zeCN=
rjJnA00TFjJqzjW0r_Jv-AdeYoJM] found a market with a non-technical incumbent=
 with an approach that was non-obvious to other startups. It had to lay two=
 foundational pieces down before executing on its master plan.=C2=A0
Its first decision, which is common among startups, was to be product-and-e=
ngineering first. The incumbent had a distribution advantage -- it worked w=
ith most of the large enterprise companies -- so Truework had to win on pro=
duct. It built a team of top product, engineering, security, and marketing =
talent from Airbnb, Coinbase, Stripe, Gusto, LinkedIn, Patreon, and Faceboo=
k.=C2=A0
From that base, Truework has executed against a master plan to grow its Ins=
tant network. Get more Verifiers on the platform to attract more Employers,=
 use more employers to attract more Verifiers, use those Verifiers to attra=
ct HR and Payroll Platforms, and so on. It=E2=80=99s Truework=E2=80=99s Fly=
wheel, and its network effect.
To learn about Truework=E2=80=99s execution against its master plan, Regula=
tory Counter-Positioning, and Building the Verified Identity Layer of the i=
nternet=E2=80=A6
